                    <span>This book is a definite must have especially if you're a disaffected conservative like myself ready to leave the Republican building and would like to join the progressive cause. Moreover, if you're sick and tired of a wimpy Democratic Party that relies on corporate donations and internal polling to run campaigns and progressives with no unity , which has been the case for 50+ years, and would like to reform the Party and unite the progressives, this book is the cure. Courage and framing, not money and polling, are what Lakoff correctly proves that conservatives used to succeed and would be well worth a strategy for Democrats and progressives to follow if at all they want to be relevant, much less in the majority.
<br />
<br />The only people who would hate this book are closed-minded conservatives who endlessly rant and complain that Democrats and progressives have nothing to offer while at the same time accepting lie after lie from Bush, Rove, Limbaugh, etc ... And it's obvious from their immature negative reviewers that they're fearful of others finally realizing that all the hoodwinking and cheating conservatives have been so good at with their seductive framing is about to meet its match and that folks is honest framing with courage. That alone makes this book a must read.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">The cat is out of the bag!</div>
                    <div>
